annotationA: AT28215p; Pyridoxamine-phosphate oxidase activity; FMN binding. It is involved in the biological process described with: oxidation-reduction process; pyridoxine biosynthetic process
annotationB: Pyridoxal kinase is the enzyme that generates Pyridoxal-5-phosphate, the metabolically active form of vitamin B6. It contributes to chromosome integrity and glucose homeostasis
